0.title: The Gift
0.plot: The kids get snowed in at MacKendrick and learn the meaning of Christmas. And they meet a mysterious new student, Linc.

1.title: Think
1.plot: Sun Hi desperately wants a band, and with both Jodi and Corki too busy, Sun Hi decides to throw open auditions... which go terribly! Isn't there anyone in MacKendrick who's good enough? Linc Harrison, whom Sun Hi met during the holidays, sure seems to think so. In fact, he's downright positive that he's the front man to Sun Hi's new band. Meanwhile Corki puts the finishing touches on her "Think Fest" project - a cute robot named "Chip." Jodi begins her internship at Hye Jung Ko's boutique - it's a killer opportunity for her, and a chance to learn from the best, as ...

2.title: Robomania
2.plot: Sun Hi ends her open auditions with a frustrated rant - which goes viral online, accidentally alienating all her fans! Now she, Sun Hi, has to apologize - yikes. After trying (and failing) to make amends, Sun Hi stages a show at Club Ry Ri, but nobody shows up! That is, until Linc offers to save the day... sort of. Meanwhile, Jodi is so overwhelmed by her internship for Hye Jung that she accidentally blows off a date with Caleb. And Corki begins to feel the heat of competition from the other students entering the "Think Fest" qualifiers - and especially from Valerie. ...

3.title: My Way or The Highway
3.plot: Sun Hi desperately wants to enter a cool new band competition called "Band Blast," but she needs a band to do it! So Linc suggests they enter together, combining their different talents, and totally opposite styles. But Sun Hi and Linc can't seem to agree on music, costumes, anything! Will they be able to put aside their differences long enough to kill it on stage? Meanwhile Caleb seeks out romantic advice from an unlikely source, and Corki's robot "Chip" disappears - who could be responsible?! Corki begins to suspect Valerie, her number one rival in the upcoming ...

4.title: Oh, Boys
4.plot: Sun Hi finds her new band partner Linc to be totally too much! They might have great on-stage chemistry, but off-stage, they're a disaster. Sun Hi seeks advice from the girls, where she learns about "The Golden Rule." Meanwhile Caleb makes a grand romantic gesture for Jodi, but will it be enough to get her attention? Jared's jealousy over Chip finally boils over, and soon both the man and the machine find themselves in a duel at high noon.

5.title: Potato Power
5.plot: Sun Hi needs to fire Linc from her new band, before she reunites with Jodi, Corki, and Caleb, for an XO-IQ concert at Club Ry Ri. Meanwhile the girls help Corki repair her robot Chip, in time to demonstrate him to the Think Fest judges. But there's some serious competition, when Valerie and Heather both reveal their own amazing science projects. Jodi and Caleb celebrate their "Textiversary" (the anniversary of their first text) at Hye Jung Ko's boutique. But when the sprinkler system activates, and the famous designer returns to see her clothing completely ruined, who...

6.title: The Mirror
6.plot: It's Family Week at MacKendrick, and everyone's parents and siblings are coming to visit! So when Sun Hi hears about all the chaos she's caused around the school - chaos she can't even remember causing - she knows just who's responsible... Meanwhile Jodi tries to fix all the ruined clothing from the sprinkler system misfire in Hye Jung's boutique, with a little help from Caleb and Heather. Jared attempts to impress Corki's father with a special magic routine, making his expensive watch disappear. But the trick works a little too well....

7.title: It's a Twin Thing
7.plot: When Sun Hi learns that Linc is putting together a new rival band called "L3", she assigns Corki on a mission to spy on Linc. But Corki's honesty and truthfulness make her pretty much the worst spy of all time. Meanwhile Jodi presents the idea of a Teen Fashion Show to Hye Jung, who thinks it's an awesome plan - and one that Jodi needs to start working on, like, pronto! Sun Hi and her twin sister Sun Mi square off in a Twin War, pulling all of MacKendrick into the fray.

8.title: Fashion 911!
8.plot: It's the day of Jodi's big Fashion Show, and everything's ready... except the clothes! Jodi needs a miracle to finish sewing in time for the big event. Now with a little help from Corki and Alex, Jodi hopes to impress designer Hye Jung, and all the fashion media that her mentor has invited. What could go wrong? Meanwhile Sun Hi pressures Caleb to write a great new hit song for XO-IQ to submit to Band Blast. But when Sun Hi's demands push Caleb over the edge, he seeks help from the master of negotiations, and Sun Hi's mortal enemy: Valerie.

9.title: Spring Fling
9.plot: Jodi unveils her new design to Hye Jung. Meanwhile, Sun Hi learns about part of Linc's background; and Corki assists Jared with his college acceptance letters.

10.title: Submission Impossible
10.plot: It's the deadline for the Band Blast submissions! But there's just one problem... XO-IQ doesn't have a submission video! Sun Hi, Corki, and Heather rush to create a new video any way they can, before the 5PM deadline. Meanwhile, Jodi and Caleb hurry to submit the rest of the submission package to DJ Maxwell, but upon arrival at his radio studio, Jodi gets trapped in the elevator... with another guy. It's all down to the wire - will XO-IQ and L3 get their Band Blast submissions to the DJ in time?

11.title: Scuttlebutt
11.plot: When Jodi hears a rumor involving her and Darmala, she's desperate to quash all the whispers before they can grow any bigger. Meanwhile, Sun Hi and Linc await the arrival of the Band Blast acceptance letters from DJ Maxwell. But Sun Hi is horrified to learn that L3 secured a spot in the contest, while XO-IQ didn't make the cut! Corki wants to spend some quality time with Jared before his upcoming graduation, but in classic Jared fashion, all he wants to do is hit the gym.

12.title: Triangles
12.plot: Sun Hi struggles with pre-Band-Blast jitters. But when she confides in Mr. Stark, he's only too happy to overwhelm her with advice and mentorship - and the only way Sun Hi can escape Stark's good intentions is by pulling Linc into the fray. Meanwhile, Heather helps Caleb to reclaim Jodi's attention, and Corki and Jared try to recruit a MacKendrick roadie crew for their big trip to Band Blast.

13.title: Get on the Bus!
13.plot: It's finally the morning of the big trip to Band Blast, and XO-IQ, L3, and all their supportive fans begin loading up the bus. But after Heather has a premonition in which the Band Blast trip meets impending doom, Linc and Sun Hi realize that Jodi and Alex are missing! With half of their bands nowhere to be found, will they even make it to the competition on time? Meanwhile, Corki and Jared stage a trial "long-distance relationship," to test how well "Jorki" will survive, after Jared leaves for college.

14.title: Reality Bites
14.plot: After XO-IQ and L3 arrive at the fabulous hotel hosting the Band Blast competition, a film crew interviews each band member for a behind-the-scenes tell-all video. Sun Hi jumps at any chance to go on camera, but the director Stefan has his own agenda. Meanwhile, Jared realizes he never actually asked Corki to the upcoming MacKendrick prom, and now he's desperate to make a "Promposal" any way he can. Caleb keeps trying to explain to Jodi exactly what happened between him and Heather in the MacKendrick parking lot.

15.title: Band Blast Off
15.plot: The Band Blast competition has finally begun, and both XO-IQ and L3 are stoked to put on the show of their lives! But the Band Blast judges begin Round One with a surprise challenge: both the MacKendrick bands will have to sing... together! Can these two bands ever find a way to take the stage as one, or will their off-stage bickering and hijinks ruin their chances at Band Blast, before the competition has even started?

16.title: Staged and Confused
16.plot: On the day of the Band Blast finals, Sun Hi tries to focus after yesterday's on-stage drama. She suspects that Linc is trying to distract her, but she's determined to win at all costs. Meanwhile Caleb and Jodi get their first taste of the competition, when they hear a rival school band playing one of XO-IQ's songs! Corki hopes to get her groove back before the big show, even while her relationship with Jared keeps shifting her eyes off the prize.

17.title: Excess Baggage
17.plot: On the way home from Band Blast, the MacKendrick teens make a pit stop in a small town. But when the bus won't start up again, they all fear the worst; what if XO-IQ doesn't make it to their big show? What if Valerie misses her one and only prom? What if they're stuck in this small town auto garage... forever? Meanwhile Sun Hi searches for a way to contact Julie Greensteel, the self-described star-maker who could propel XO-IQ to worldwide fame, while Corki second-guesses her relationship status with Jared.

18.title: Im-Prom-Tu
18.plot: The MacKendrick teens decide to stage their own prom, using every trick they know to make it a magical night. But for Sun Hi, there's just one problem; Linc has already agreed to go to prom with Valerie!! If Sun Hi can't have the prom of her dreams, maybe no one should! Meanwhile, Heather and Caleb string together potato batteries to power the prom lights, while Jared spies on Corki, landing them both in a sticky situation. For XO-IQ and L3, it's a romantic MacKendrick prom that they'll never forget...

19.title: Looking for Trouble
19.plot: Nick Cannon guest stars, as Sun Hi, Jodi, Corki, and Caleb prepare for their biggest show yet, called "MacKendrick Tonight." Stefan leads a TV crew, who will broadcast XO-IQ's concert out to the universe and launch them into worldwide fame!... If they can just find a place to perform. Meanwhile Sun Hi suspects Linc of withholding a secret from her; what's he hiding? Jodi hopes to uncover the meaning behind all the looks that passed between Heather and Caleb during the prom, hoping their relationship can survive... And just as the band prepares to take the stage, ...

20.title: Really? It's Over?
20.plot: Nick Cannon guest stars, in a Make It Pop! Season Finale, as XO-IQ tries desperately to take the stage one last time. This is it - they need to perform for the "MacKendrick Tonight" TV crew, and for Julie Greensteel, the musical star-maker who could launch their careers. Problem is, Principal Diona has forbidden them from performing. Now as romantic tensions mount, can the band pull it together in time to impress Nick Cannon, Julie, and their national TV audience? Meanwhile, there's an offer on the table that could change their lives...

21.title: Summer Splash Spectacular
21.plot: The gang head to a resort for the summer and perform as the hotel's exclusive house band. However, the resort manager tries to push them in a new direction, which causes some tense within the group.

1.title: Rumors & Roommates
1.plot: Sun Hi, Jodi and Corki start life at MacKendrick Prep boarding school with big expectations and bigger dreams - all of which might unravel because of a secret Corki refuses to reveal.

2.title: Duet
2.plot: Sun Hi creates a band to launch her plan for pop music world domination, but Corki won't join, in case it jeopardizes her schoolwork - or her secret. Meanwhile, Caleb finds a place they can perform, but it needs a lot of work. Is he up to it?

3.title: Failed Dreams
3.plot: While Caleb overhauls the roller rink into a dance club, Sun Hi and Jodi fail a test that puts them on academic probation. This means they can't audition for the musical.

4.title: Stolen Moves
4.plot: Valerie sneaks to the roller rink and steals Sun-Hi's and Jodi's moves for her cheer. Corki tries to find proof that Valerie stole it.

5.title: I Can't Hear Me
5.plot: Sun-Hi loses her voice before their first show.

6.title: Popular
6.plot: During homecoming week, the school is buzzing about who will run for king and queen.

7.title: The Situation
7.plot: When the boys' floor is declared toxic, the boys and girls are forced to share a dorm floor.

8.title: The Campaign
8.plot: Sun Hi and Jodi stand up to Valerie and force Corki to run against her for homecoming queen.

9.title: I Am Genius
9.plot: Sun Hi is called to the principal's office after taking an aptitude test.

10.title: Homecoming
10.plot: Caleb and the girls plot to have a secret party; Jodi and Corki attempt to figure out what to wear.

11.title: Mr. Chang
11.plot: The arrival of Corki's father jeopardizes the band's radio interview; Mr. Stark conducts auditions.

12.title: Fashion Truck
12.plot: Jodi visits her fashion idol's store; Corki must keep the band secret from her father.

13.title: Troll
13.plot: Jodi and Caleb bond while working on the musical; Jared takes charge of the play.

14.title: The Tutor
14.plot: Valerie is assigned as Jodi's tutor; Jared seeks Corki's help to turn Valerie into a better actress.

15.title: Talent Show Redux
15.plot: Corki and the play suffer when Jared takes total creative control; Mr. Stark is obsessed with fans.

16.title: The Curse of Reality
16.plot: Sun Hi curses the play and Mr. Stark when she steals his spotlight; Corki plays hard to get.

17.title: Eggs
17.plot: Relationships are tested when the students are assigned to take care of an egg for parenting class.

18.title: Love and Detention
18.plot: The group finds themselves in detention two days before the play's premiere.

19.title: Dreams
19.plot: The girls are forced to wrestle the production away from Valerie and the Spirit Squad.

20.title: XO-IQ

imdb.title: Make It Pop
plot: Sun Hi, Jodi and Corki are three girls with different personalities. Attending Mackendrick Prep, all three are randomly selected to room together. Together they must achieve stardom in Kpop while balancing school and other relationships.::TheCrypticKnight
synopsis: Make It Pop is a half-hour daily musical comedy series that follows three girls in boarding school Sun Hi, Jodi and Corki who, with the help of their aspiring DJ friend Caleb, form a pop band, and find music, mischief, fun, and friendship.
